### Automatically Generate a Table of Contents in LaTeX
To generate a table of contents (ToC) automatically in a LaTeX document, you can use the following commands:
1. **\tableofcontents**: This command generates the ToC at the beginning of the document.
2. **\addcontentsline**: This command adds an entry to the ToC for a specific section, chapter, or other element.
3. **\label**: This command creates a label for a specific section, chapter, or other element.
4. **\ref**: This command references the label created in the previous step.
Here's an example of how to use these commands:
```  
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}
\tableofcontents
\section{Introduction}
\label{sec:introduction}
This is the introduction section.
